MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: packages/shared-types/src/.+\.ts$
ADVISORY: |
  `@pecking-order/shared-types` is a **built** package, not a source import.
  After editing files in `packages/shared-types/src/`, you MUST rebuild
  before any consumer (apps/client, apps/game-server, apps/lobby,
  packages/game-cartridges) will see the changes in `tsc --noEmit`:

      cd packages/shared-types && npm run build

  Symptom when skipped: client tsc errors like "Property 'X' does not exist
  on type 'Y'" even though the field is clearly in the source you just
  edited. The fix is always the rebuild — don't re-edit the source chasing
  phantom type errors.

  If a change is load-bearing across multiple apps, rebuild before running
  each app's type-check.
